content:
Set Up a Dialog Rule Step

Use rules to specify the conditions that start any of these actions: call a dialog from within the current dialog, redirect to a different dialog, clear a variable value, transfer to an agent, and set a variable. Use rules to send targeted messages to your customers with Conditional Messaging. Rule conditions are optional.

Available in:
Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

User Permissions Needed:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

Rule actions are:

Call Dialog: Retains the context of the conversation and returns the conversation back to the original dialog after the second dialog is completed.
Clear Variable (or Clear Variable Value): Changes the variable that you specify to an unset state.
End Chat: Ends the bot conversation.
Redirect to Dialog: Interrupts the current dialog and starts another dialog.
Send Message (or Send a Message): Sends a message to the customer.
Set Language (or Set Conversation Language): Sets the language the bot uses with the end user based on a variable.
Set Routing Type: Routes the chat session to a specialized queue that you define as a context variable.
Set Variable: Copies the contents of a context variable into a variable that you define.
Transfer: Escalates the chat session to a queue, agent, or bot.

Optionally, you can create a condition sentence using a variable, an operator, and a value. If you create multiple conditions, you can use the Condition Requirements field to add AND/OR functionality. 

To add multiple rule actions, select a rule action from the Rule Action field, and then specify any required parameters.
Save the dialog.
Rule actions fire in the order shown. To change the order, drag the rule actions and save the dialog.
